  "note": "753B-param MoE (glm_moe_dsa), 1M context. DeepSeek-V3.2-style MLA with DeepSeek Sparse Attention (DSA): every layer keeps a low-rank latent KV and a lightning indexer that selects the top-k=2048 keys for the main attention. GLM-5.2's novelty is IndexShare (arXiv:2603.12201): the indexer is recomputed only once per group of index_topk_freq=4 layers ('full') and reused by the other three ('shared'), cutting per-token attention FLOPs ~2.9x at 1M context. We model this with indexer_shared on the shared layers, which still run the top-k-capped main attention but pay no indexer projection/scoring cost. First 3 layers dense FFN, remaining 75 MoE (256 routed experts, 8 active, 1 shared). The full/shared phase is reconstructed from the config's indexer_types (the public array is truncated): dense layers 0-2 each compute their own index, then each block of 4 MoE layers computes the index on its first layer.",
